.TH "input_scancode_to_scalar" 9 "input_scancode_to_scalar" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
input_scancode_to_scalar \- converts scancode in &struct input_keymap_entry
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" input_scancode_to_scalar
.BI "(const struct input_keymap_entry *ke "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *scancode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ke" 12
keymap entry containing scancode to be converted.
.IP "scancode" 12
pointer to the location where converted scancode should
be stored.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is used to convert scancode stored in \fIstruct keymap_entry\fP
into scalar form understood by legacy keymap handling methods. These
methods expect scancodes to be represented as 'unsigned int'.
